task.summary: - Fixed major bugs - Removed LocalInstitution class after realizing that the Institution class inheriting from ParseObject is Parcelable - Moved the requestStudents method to the LoginSection, so that it is available to all parts of the application - The student Institution class and the Student class not each have their own getProfileImageUrl method, instead of sharing the one in the ParseUser Object

- Fixed bug which made the ChatMessageRepository subscribe the conversations to the ParseLiveQuery Twice by adding mutex locks and static blocks - Removed `GetInnerFields` Callable, which would fetch nested ParseObjects since parse already includes the `include(CLASS_NAME)` method to solve this problem - Increased the size of my background threadPool to 4: Planned support to make this a variable number depending on the Amount of Traffic - Inlined some variables and cleaned up code for readability
-Added a Group Participants section in the MVVM design pattern -Added notifications for when a group message arrives
-Rewrote signup section with better error handling
- Wrote tests for the BoundedPriorityQueue and BisectRightMethod - Wrote a ParallelVpTree implementation
- Wrote tests for the BoundedPriorityQueue and BisectRightMethod - Wrote a ParallelVpTree implementation
-Added ClusterActivity for performing actual clustering. -Removed dead code from VP Tree. -Changed my string comparison method from damerauLevenshtein to a normalized version of it.

MESSAGE.value: Wrote a new SimpleState<T> class to convey data to the UI. Fixed bugs on the User Profile Page.

Wrote functionality to handle new messages using multiple background threads. Since ParseLiveQuery cannot handle nested queries, which would be used to filter which messages for conversations the user is in, I manually subscribe each conversation to the liveQueryClient
